spanishExample: Creí que justo tenía su lista.
englishTranslation: I thought she just had her list.

spanishExample: Creía que esta era la realidad, pero ahora no lo creo.
englishTranslation: I used to think this was the reality, but now I don’t believe it.

spanishExample: Ella cree que tenemos que pensarlo.
englishTranslation: She thinks we have to think about it.

spanishExample: Ella pensaba en lo que tú piensas ahora.
englishTranslation: She used to think about what you think (about) now.

spanishExample: En ese momento pensó en hacerlo.
englishTranslation: At that moment she thought about doing it.

spanishExample: Espero que piense en su seguridad.
englishTranslation: I hope she thinks about her safety.

spanishExample: Estoy pensando en hacer algo rápido en el juego de mesa.
englishTranslation: I’m thinking about doing something quickly in the board game.

spanishExample: No estamos pensando en ti.
englishTranslation: We aren’t thinking about you.

spanishExample: No puedo creer que lo hizo medio bien.
englishTranslation: I can’t believe that she did it kind of well.

spanishExample: No quiere que yo piense en eso, porque lo creía.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want me to think about that, because I used to believe it.

spanishExample: Pensamos en nosotros.
englishTranslation: We are thinking about ourselves.

spanishExample: Pensé en la guerra, o en algo peor.
englishTranslation: I thought about war, or about something worse.

spanishExample: Quiero que pienses esto para que lo puedas creer.
englishTranslation: I want you to think this so you can believe it.

spanishExample: Siempre pensamos, pero nunca hablamos acerca de eso.
englishTranslation: We always think, but we never talk about that.

spanishExample: Siempre piensa, pero no tiene que pensar.
englishTranslation: She always thinks, but she doesn’t have to think.

spanishExample: Supongo que tú y yo no pensamos igual.
englishTranslation: I guess you and I don’t think the same.

spanishExample: Yo creía lo mismo que crees ahora.
englishTranslation: I used to believe the same thing you believe now.

spanishExample: ¡Cree que puedes hacerlo!
englishTranslation: Believe that you can do it!

spanishExample: ¡Créeme! Tienes que creerlo.
englishTranslation: Believe me! You have to believe it.

spanishExample: ¡Jamás lo pienses!
englishTranslation: Don’t ever think about it!

spanishExample: ¡Piensa! ¡No puedes hacer eso!
englishTranslation: Think! You can’t do that!

spanishExample: ¡Piénsalo otra vez! No lo pensaste nada.
englishTranslation: Think it again! You didn’t think it at all.

spanishExample: ¡Piense en su trabajo!
englishTranslation: (Formal) Think about your job!
